I work next door and plan to frequent this place. They're on Ritual, GrubHub, Doordash etc apps. This place rocks! I've been working near the Loop for over five years and I have been to all the ethnic joints. Good price, great food. If you never tried Indian/Pakistani food, this is a good start. Anything with beef, like the goshat. Drink it down with a mango lassi to cure the spices. The naan is the best in the Loop. Always fresh but never large enough. If you show up around noon, be prepared to wait. Best time is after one.

So good to have an Indian semi-fast food restaurant within walking distance of the loop, and with such nice outdoor seating available, as well (don't let the Maps photo fool you).  Been to Baba's several times -- the Chicken Curry is a favorite and nicely spicy, but no more than you'd find at a typical mexican place.  Prices are similar to other lunch places around (Roti, Chipotle, etc), and the inside dining space is equivalent.  Each meal is prepared as you order, a plus over Chutney Joe's, which is also good.  Be sure to try their creamy chutney in the convenient bottles -- goes great with the rice, or on the curry dishes, and is similar to a lighter version of sour cream with cucumber (will take the edge off of spice, in case you like your meals milder).
